item.title: Need Someone To Help
item.dc:creator: @homerunhitta977 homerunhitta977
item.description:
@homerunhitta977 wrote:

This is what we need help with:

Where do I edit in my client files to put my server online for others to play? I want to be able to upload it to uppit and have others play it… what do I change? I’m already portforwarded, everything is set, I have a no-ip online, I just need to know where to insert my no-ip URL and how to make the server public for a download client. I need to know what to change in what files in order to put it online so if I upload the client to uppit.com and tell my friend about it, he can download it and also play it. Someone please help me with this step by step?

We’ve tried going into client.java and editing the “server =” to our no-ip and it won’t work. We need someone to go to our site and teamview my friend who is hosting the download client so we can make the server public.

Site: http://evolution-pk.net
